def_en: If one thing is unlike another thing, the two things have different qualities or characteristics from each other.
You can use unlike to contrast two people, things, or situations, and show how they are different.

def_cn: 与…平时不同；不像…平常那样
def_en: If you describe something that a particular person has done as being unlike them, you mean that you are surprised by it because it is not typical of their character or normal behaviour.
